00:46:29.940 --> 00:46:32.590
You are jumping up and down.

00:46:32.590 --> 00:46:36.900
&gt;&gt; How do you think of names for
people who didn't really exist?

00:46:36.900 --> 00:46:38.500
&gt;&gt; Raina Telgemeier:
That's a good question.

00:46:38.500 --> 00:46:43.940
Catrina is named after La
Catrina which is an illustration

00:46:43.940 --> 00:46:47.830
of a skeleton lady that was
done by a guy named Posada

00:46:47.830 --> 00:46:51.560
and so she's actually a
very famous paint or image.

00:46:51.560 --> 00:46:55.060
And then Maya's name comes from--
I've met a lot of kids named Maya

00:46:55.060 --> 00:46:56.360
and they're always
kind of like cute.

00:46:56.360 --> 00:46:57.660 position:56%
They're usually jumping up and down.

00:46:57.660 --> 00:46:59.970
And I just think Maya
is an awesome name.

00:46:59.970 --> 00:47:02.460
And Callie comes from
the State of California,

00:47:02.460 --> 00:47:03.760
which is really embarrassing.

00:47:03.760 --> 00:47:06.240
I don't know if the adults will
notice this song "Going Back

00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:12.620
To Cali" by LL Cool J. I was--
When I was brainstorming that book,

00:47:12.620 --> 00:47:16.000
I was in the car like driving
around my parents' neighborhood

00:47:16.000 --> 00:47:17.390
and that song came on
the radio and I was

00:47:17.390 --> 00:47:19.460
like that's it, her name is Callie.

