Hi.

00:47:48.320 --> 00:47:52.590
&gt;&gt; What happens when
you get writer's block?

00:47:52.590 --> 00:47:53.890
&gt;&gt; Raina Telgemeier: Good question.

00:47:53.890 --> 00:47:57.150 position:56%
Probably the same thing that
happens when you get writer's block,

00:47:57.150 --> 00:47:58.670
you're just like what
am I going to do?

00:47:58.670 --> 00:48:01.360
So sometimes I just try to step
away from my desk for a while.

00:48:01.360 --> 00:48:06.050
So I go to the beach or I go hiking
in the mountains or I get in my car

00:48:06.050 --> 00:48:09.880
and I drive around and I listen
to LL Cool J. But you know what,

00:48:09.880 --> 00:48:11.980
inspiration is everywhere
and you'll never know

00:48:11.980 --> 00:48:14.010
when something is going
to inspire you.

00:48:14.010 --> 00:48:17.720 position:56%
So, I try to read a lot of books, I
try to watch a lot of TV and movies,

00:48:17.720 --> 00:48:20.640
I try to meet lots of
people and go lots of places

00:48:20.640 --> 00:48:23.320
and things inspire me everywhere.

00:48:23.320 --> 00:48:26.670
&gt;&gt; Good to know.

00:48:26.670 --> 00:48:29.600
&gt;&gt; Are you afraid of ghosts?

00:48:29.600 --> 00:48:32.090
&gt;&gt; Raina Telgemeier: I don't know
if I believe that ghosts exist.

00:48:32.090 --> 00:48:34.720
So it's hard to be afraid of
something that doesn't exist.

00:48:34.720 --> 00:48:41.790
Yeah. If I knew they did exist,
I'd be extremely afraid of them.

00:48:41.790 --> 00:48:43.200
That's why they look like snakes.

00:48:43.200 --> 00:48:47.030
Did you notice the-- so maybe
there's a connection there.

00:48:47.030 --> 00:48:48.330
Hi.

00:48:48.330 --> 00:48:49.890
&gt;&gt; How much books have you wrote?

00:48:49.890 --> 00:48:51.190
&gt;&gt; Raina Telgemeier:
I've written eight books.

00:48:51.190 --> 00:48:54.380
That's four "Baby-Sitters Club"
books and then "Smile," "Drama,"

00:48:54.380 --> 00:48:56.420
"Sisters," and, wait, "Ghosts."

00:48:56.420 --> 00:48:57.910
Did I say that one?

00:48:57.910 --> 00:49:00.180
Yeah, eight books total.

00:49:00.180 --> 00:49:01.760
&gt;&gt; That's a lot.

00:49:01.760 --> 00:49:06.380
&gt;&gt; Raina Telgemeier:
Thank you, thank you.

